original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. You can insert this into your terminal output as follows:

```
\033[32mYour Text Here\033[0m
```

In this case, `\033` represents the start of the escape sequence, `[32]` specifies the green color, `Your Text Here` is where you put the text you want to display in green, and `\033[0m` resets the terminal color back to default after displaying the colored text. Remember, this won't actually change the appearance until viewed through a compatible terminal emulator supporting ANSI escape codes.
